    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Rabin Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      COPD patients requiring ventilation may benefit from invasive or non invasive ventilation.
      Non invasive ventilation is often incompatible with oral or enteral feding, due to gastric
      dilatation and full mask therapy. At the other hand, invasive ventilation is associated with
      incomplete enteral feeding and nutrition requirements are not reached. The aim of the study
      was to compare the feeding delivery of COPD patients receiving invasive or non invasive
      mechanical ventilation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
